</paragraph>
<caption id="DC077FEA45BCF708F40565EE89D9DE12" doi="10.3897/herpetozoa.35.e80151.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/654720" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="3BB5E385A2FE9F776CF6BD2A1EAEFDA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="CD091C9CCD0B7BF8580FA894B5AAED11" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3281F33F8AF5B6B6857617FD1F29A23C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">A.</emphasis>
The general aspect of the adult male specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="15A1961B8713A0213D19F929D7D6824B" authorityName="Siler, Heitz, Davis, Freitas, Aowphol, Termprayoon &amp; Grismer" authorityYear="2018" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygosoma siamense" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siamense">
<emphasis id="0C08C7F7CC18BD8C1539009A757B24EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Lygosoma siamense</emphasis>
